The Texas legislature recently passed a new law aimed at making it more difficult for Texans, particularly citizens of color, to vote. This law restricts the voting options that were previously used to ensure safe voting in the last election. The author of the article met with Texas lawmakers who fought against this bill and praises their efforts to protect democracy. The author calls on Congress to pass the For the People Act and the John Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act to safeguard the voting rights of all Americans.